It’s Ashton’s 4th birthday today. Never in my life did I imagine I would be visiting my son on his birthday. Only 25 minutes together in a hallway. Sometimes we have to make life choices that we know are going to suck but we don’t realize just how bad they suck until we’re in the middle of the sucky parts. A cupcake shop opened up early for me and I was hit with a wave of sadness and started sobbing in that shop. The man working the counter came around and hugged me while I cried. I can’t share the progress without the real. This is as real as it gets. Having to share your kids is the fucking worst sometimes.

I woke up yesterday morning with the water damn near audibly calling my name. So I listened and I’m so glad I did. A woman passing by made a comment that all the animals were flocking to me. I didn’t realize it at first. Dragonflies and butterflies all around, one of the gators swam right by me (always a heart racing but surreal moment), the manatees were finding me and hanging out up at the top of the water instead of at the bottom like they usually do. One manatee swam alongside my kayak for at least 5 minutes. I felt like the Snow White of the river. I’m so grateful for these experiences.
